Upon completion of the course, students should be able to
- Perform essential calculations in matrices, determinants, and linear systems;
- Use these calculations in the context of certain business and scientific applications;
- Realize the importance of linear algebra in a broad spectrum of subject areas;
- Prepare for undergraduate studies requiring statistical knowledge.

